discoveries.explanation: Beautiful match between self-propelled particles and flocking! Physics describes autonomous units interacting through forces, biology describes three-zone interaction rules. Both explain how local interactions between moving entities create emergent collective patterns.
discoveries.pattern: Self-propelled agents with zone-based interactions creating collective motion

discoveries.explanation: Information networks shaping collective outcomes matches biological self-organization. Both describe how structure and dynamics of local interactions determine global behavior without central control.

Stochastic pulsing in biology matches phase transition in physics! Individual cells randomly pulse below threshold then collectively synchronize above it - identical to Kuramoto oscillators transitioning to synchrony at critical coupling.
discoveries.pattern: Threshold-driven phase transition from disorder to synchronization

discoveries.explanation: Robot swarms developing specialized roles matches biological stigmergy. Both describe distributed problem-solving through environment modification and local interactions without central planning.
Neural circuits generating sustained/oscillatory responses matches spatial pattern emergence in excitable cells. Both involve local excitable dynamics producing emergent spatiotemporal patterns.
discoveries.paper_2: Spatial pattern emergence from local excitable dynamics

discoveries.explanation: Individual heterogeneity structuring collective dynamics! Animal personality differences (bold/shy, fast/slow) create heterogeneous interaction networks that shape group behavior - key insight that diversity drives collective patterns.

Network topology constraining dynamics meets small-world enhancing synchronization. Complementary aspects - general principle that structure shapes dynamics, specific case of shortcuts improving sync.

Rate-dependent tipping matches noise-induced attractor hopping. Two complementary mechanisms for sudden transitions - one from parameter change rate, other from stochastic fluctuations between basins.
discoveries.pattern: Multiple pathways to sudden system transitions

discoveries.explanation: Climate tipping points from two perspectives! Earth science focuses on self-reinforcing feedbacks past thresholds, climate science distinguishes noise vs critical transitions. Together they form complete picture of climate instability.
discoveries.pattern: Climate system tipping through feedbacks and critical transitions
discoveries.paper_1: Critical thresholds trigger self-reinforcing climate state
discoveries.paper_2: Tipping points: Early warning and wishful thinking

discoveries.explanation: Animal personality differences structuring groups matches robot role differentiation. Both show how heterogeneity (innate or emergent) in individual behavior creates organized collective dynamics.
Clustering amplifying cascades meets small-world enhancing sync. Both describe how network structure modifications (adding triangles vs shortcuts) fundamentally change spreading dynamics.
discoveries.pattern: Network structural features amplifying dynamical processes

discoveries.explanation: Multi-scale averaging in optical cascades matches biological emergence across scales! Both describe how processes at one scale average out to create emergent dynamics at higher scales - beautiful cross-domain principle.
discoveries.paper_2: Multiscale emergence from individual to population

discoveries.explanation: Zonal interaction rules meet individual heterogeneity. Shows how both spatial structure (zones) and individual differences shape collective animal behavior - complementary organizing principles.
discoveries.pattern: Spatial zones and individual variation structuring collectives
